For our Final Happy Tail of #2017 - Let's check in with Dazzle!
Dazzle was originally adopted from Greenhill Humane Society in 2002, but 13 years later, her family could no longer care for her. And because we're committed to each of our Animals for life, with a heavy heart, we welcomed her back.
It took 685 days in our care, and several slow, patient introductions, but Dazzle's Mom finally won her over earlier this year!

Here's what she says, "Dazzle has settled in, she's a lap cat, sleeps in my bed...but she's a cranky old lady and wants to eat or she shreds newspaper...but it's funny and I love her!" The love we give is free, but we need your help to provide safe shelter, healthy food, medical care, behavior training and adoption services for thousands of Animals that will need our help in the coming year - We've thankfully met our goal of $18,000 for 2018, but let's see how much we can raise together by Midnight!?! Please give your final, most generous, year-end tax-deductible gift now #linkinbio
And from all the Pets and People of @greenhillhumane and First Avenue Shelter...
Thank You for your Support and Have a Furry Happy New Year!!

It's Tank Time!
In our care for over 550 days - Tank found his forever family earlier this year - and boy did he hit the jackpot!
Tank is an extraordinary soul - but he also had extraordinary medical issues - and it took a team of veterinarians, specialists and animal care staff to provide the care he needed to enjoy a reasonable quality of life for nearly 2 years.
Conditions treated / managed at Greenhill Humane Society included severe arthritis in multiple joints, suspected cruciate tear in both knees, severe dry eye with painful corneal damage/disease requiring long term medication, chronic ear infections, and something (suspected allergies) that made his skin red and painful. He despised taking oral medication which makes treatment of his conditions challenging and was selectively reactive towards other animals. So, we got creative... he lived in our Admin offices to reduce his stress/anxiety from being kenneled with other dogs, and his feeding/medication routine was inventive to say the least.

The love we give is free, but the medical care and behavioral rehabilitation that we provide to thousands of animals each year takes money - it takes support from you.
Please make a year-end tax-deductible gift now so that we can help more animals in 2018 #linkinbio
Here's what Tank's new family has to say:
"Tank is doing wonderful! He is well mannered, well behaved. He is spoiled ROTTEN, has two beds, and more toys than most kids get at Christmas. He is a joy to have! The vet was very impressed with him, and the vet techs were following him on Facebook so they were very happy to meet him. He is getting all his meds and we have him on the special diet for his allergies. The vet removed his skin tag so now he is even more beautiful. He has had no problems in the house or the yard. He does great with other people. When I walk him, people often stop me to ask if it is Tank. He needed a place to spend his golden years and we are glad to have him. He is happy and sassy and he is doing GH proud!â€

Happy New Year from Tank, Jeff and Kathy.
"I think he is finally feeling we are his forever home. He is a very lovable furry family member." If you'd like to help more animals like Tank in 2018 - please show your support by making a year-end tax-deductible donation before Midnight Tonight #linkinbio

STARK is available for adoption here at Cat Love Rescue. This cutie is timid and shy, but with a gentle pet he allows you to pet him. He would do best in a quiet home with no children. If he sounds like the right cat for you please contact us for more information and how you can set up a meet and greet in Chino Hills, CA. -- All of our rescue kittens are in foster homes, spayed/neutered, fully vaccinated, tested for FeLV & FIV, dewormed, treated for flea prevention, and fitted with a microchip.
